# triangular

$$
k = n*(n+1)/2
2*k = n^2 + n
0 = n^2 + n - 2*k
$$
need
$$
1 - 4*(-2*k)
=
1+8*k
$$
to be a square.
If so, it is even and
$$
(1 + \sqrt(1+8*k)) / 2
$$
works.

# pentagonal

$$
k = n*(3*n-1)/2
2*k = 3*n^2 - n
0 = 3*n^2 - n - 2*k
$$
Need
$$
1 - 4*3*(-2*k)
1 + 24*k
$$
a square.
Then,
$$
(1 + sqrt(1+24*k)) / 6
$$

#hexagonal

$$
0 = 2*n^2 - n - k
$$
Need
$$
1 - 4*2*(-k)
1 + 8*k
$$
Get
$$
(1 + sqrt(1+8*k)) / 4
$$

# heptagonal

$$
5*n^2 -3*n - 2*k = 0
$$
$$
9 - 4*5*(-2)*k
9 + 40*k
$$
and
$$
(3 + sqrt(9+40*k)) / 10
$$

# octagonal

$$
3*n^2 - 2*n - k = 0
$$
$$
4 - 4(3)(-k)
4 + 12k
$$
$$
(2 + 2sqrt(1+3k)) / (2*3)
(1 + sqrt(1+3k) / 3)
$$
